The shrine was also a center of samurai devotion. {{ill|Minamoto no Yoritomo|ja|源頼朝|qq=draft|qq=draft}} is said to have prayed here for the safe childbirth of his wife, {{ill|Hōjō Masako|ja|北条政子|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. During the {{ill|Sengoku period|ja|戦国時代|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, the {{ill|Later Hōjō clan|ja|後北条氏|qq=draft|qq=draft}} donated a small piece of land to the shrine.

The shrine stands in the former village of {{ill|Koma Village|ja|高麗村|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, later incorporated into {{ill|Ōiso Town|ja|大磯町|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.

== Enshrined Deities ==
